  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The inventory_kpi_monthly view (source: inventory_transactions) has dimensions: snapshot_date, product_category, production_line. Measures: avg_on_hand, avg_spoilage_rate, avg_fill_rate, avg_freshness, total_near_expiry. The waste_kpi_monthly view (source: shelf_life_snapshots) has dimensions: perf_month, product_category, optimization_action. Measures: total_spoiled, total_spoilage_cost, avg_turnover, avg_shelf_remaining, item_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. product_id, product_name).",
